having the potential to impact negatively on women, children and heterosexuals in general irrespective of the short and long term impact on the men themselves It makes no sense that 92% of man in CAR believe divorce should be avoided, but 44% of men believe that where family are financially at risk and they would not be able avoid that risk but the wife can, then divorce is acceptable. It’s very unlikely that a man could meet the needs of his wife and he shouldn’t leave her high and dry. Does that reflect the position held by his family back home? Do his parents and family recognise him in need of financial support however stressed or challenged they may be in their own family needs, including large numbers of orphans? It’s important to recognise that not just the family back home needs support. The children of the family left behind are dependent on the integrity and honour of dad.

It must also be recognised that more than 50% of women under 30 in CAR have no education and have fled the country with more than 500,000 refugees or internally displaced people According to a recent article, women under 30 “represent almost 50 per cent of the 215,000 people in Bangui and the surrounding areas who have sought refuge at displacement sites over the violence in CAR in recent weeks”.
